						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The real zapper trigger generates a trigger-on signal only for a few frames after you pull it, doesn't matter how long you hold it down.</div><br />No it doesn't - I have a real Zapper (one of the orange ones), and if you pull the trigger slowly until it makes a soft click it sends trigger-on as long as you hold it there, but if you pull it the rest of the way it will click much more loudly and <em>clear</em> the trigger signal. It's sort of like a double-action revolver, where the trigger-on signal corresponds to the hammer being pulled back all the way.</div>

					
