			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I discovered something important about the problem with Lethal Weapon (Ch) [U][!].unf: The color of the pixel at the mouse coordinates on the frame prior to the white-silhouettes frame determines the response rather than the white-silhouette.  In other words, it's reacting too early.<br /><br />That explains why it hits the target only 20% of the time.  It was varying based on the pixel color that I happened to click on.  <br /><br />It'll study this further.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

